claim.claim-text:
14. A compound filter cartridge for filtering fluids comprising: 
a) carbonaceous filter element surrounding a void, said carbonaceous filter element having a fluid entry port located proximal to an outer portion of said carbonaceous filter element; 
b) a cage positioned in said carbonaceous filter element void; 
c) a selectively permeable fiber bundle positioned in said cage for receiving fluid passing through said carbonaceous filter element into said carbonaceous filter element void, said fiber bundle comprising a plurality of hollow, microporous fibers each having a first open end and a second open end, at least said first open-end being potted in a sealing compound, anterior to said cage and said carbonaceous filter element, such that said first open end is exposed on an outer end face of said sealing compound body permitting fluid entering said hollow, microporous fibers to exit through said outer end face of said sealing compound body; and 
wherein said cage has sufficient openwork such that more than about 40% of the surface area of said selectively permeable fiber bundle is in direct contact with fluid when fluid fills said carbonaceous filter element void.

28. A compound filter cartridge for filtering fluids comprising: 
a) carbonaceous filter element surrounding a void approximately concentric with a central axis of said carbonaceous filter element, said carbonaceous filter element having a fluid entry port located proximal to an outer portion of said carbonaceous filter element; 
b) a perforated jacket positioned in said carbonaceous filter element void in a manner approximately con centric with s aid central axis of said carbonaceous filter element; 
c) a selectively permeable fiber bundle positioned in said perforated jacket for receiving fluid passing through said carbonaceous filter element into said carbonaceous filter element void, said fiber bundle comprising a plurality of hollow, microporous fibers each having a first open end and a second open end, at least said first open-end being potted in a sealing compound such that said first open end is exposed on an outer end face of said sealing compound body permitting fluid entering said hollow, microporous fibers to exit through said outer end face of said sealing compound body; and 
wherein said perforated jacket has sufficient perforations such that more than about 40% of the surface area of said selectively permeable fiber bundle is in direct contact with fluid when fluid fills said carbonaceous filter element void. A filtration device as recited in claim 25, wherein said filter element is defined at least in part by an extruded carbon block.

34. A compound filter cartridge for filtering fluids comprising: 
a) a pre-filter element for filtering course particulates surrounding a void, said pre-filter element having a fluid entry port located proximal to an outer portion of said pre-filter element; 
b) a carbonaceous filter element positioned in said pre-filter element void, said carbonaceous filter element surrounding a carbonaceous filter element void; 
c) a selectively permeable fiber bundle positioned in said carbonaceous filter element void for receiving fluid passing through said carbonaceous filter element into said carbonaceous filter element void, said fiber bundle comprising a plurality of hollow, microporous fibers each having a first open end and a second open end, wherein said first and second open-end are potted in a sealing compound in such a manner that said first open end and said second open end of each of said hollow fibers are exposed on an outer end face of said sealing compound body permitting fluid entering said hollow, microporous fibers to exit through said outer end face of said sealing compound body.
